    "#### 3) Use the **input()** function to receive an input in the form **'68.4 1.71'**, that is, two floating point numbers in a line separated by space. Then, assign these numbers to the variables ** p ** and ** h ** respectively, which represent an individual's weight and height (hint: take a look at the '.split ()' method). With this data, calculate the individual's Body Mass Index (BMI) from the following relationship: \n",
    "    \n",
    "\\begin{equation}\n",
    "BMI = \\dfrac{weight}{height^2}\n",
    "\\end{equation}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x = input()\n",
    "split_var = x.split()\n",
    "p = float(split_var[0])\n",
    "h = float(split_var[1])\n",
    "bmi_formula = p/h ** 2\n",
    "print(\"Your BMI = \", bmi_formula)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### This value can also be classified according to ranges of values, following to the table below. Use conditional structures to classify and print the classification assigned to the individual. \n",
    "\n",
    "<center><img src=\"https://healthtravelguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Body-mass-index-table.png\" width=\"30%\"><\\center>  \n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "(source: https://healthtravelguide.com/bmi-calculator/)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x = input()\n",
    "split_var = x.split()\n",
    "p = float(split_var[0])\n",
    "h = float(split_var[1])\n",
    "bmi_formula = p/h ** 2\n",
    "if bmi_formula < 18.5:\n",
    "    print(\"Your BMI (Underweight) = \", bmi_formula)\n",
    "elif bmi_formula >= 18.5 and bmi_formula < 24.9:\n",
    "    print(\"Your BMI (Normal weight) = \", bmi_formula)\n",
    "elif bmi_formula >= 25.0 and bmi_formula < 29.9:\n",
    "    print(\"Your BMI (Pre-obesity) = \", bmi_formula)\n",
    "elif bmi_formula >= 30.0 and bmi_formula < 34.9:\n",
    "    print(\"Your BMI (Obesity class I) = \", bmi_formula)\n",
    "elif bmi_formula >= 35.0 and bmi_formula < 39.9:\n",
    "    print(\"Your BMI (Obesity class II) = \", bmi_formula)\n",
    "elif bmi_formula >= 40.0:\n",
    "    print(\"Your BMI (Obesity class III) = \", bmi_formula)"
   ]
  },
